      <div id="list"><article class="finding" data-domain="Web" data-severity="Critical" data-text="kb-1 sql injection user input is concatenated into sql statements. full database compromise, data exfiltration. use parameterized queries / orm; least-privilege db accounts. cwe-89 a03:2021 injection">
    <button class="finding-head" type="button">
      <span><b>kb-1</b> SQL Injection</span>
      <span class="sev critical">Critical</span>
    </button>
    <div class="finding-body">
      <div class="meta"><span>Web</span><span>Injection and unsafe parsing</span><span>CWE-89</span><span>A03:2021 Injection</span></div>
      <h3>Behavior</h3><p>User input is concatenated into SQL statements.</p>
      <h3>Risk</h3><p>Full database compromise, data exfiltration.</p>
      <h3>How to identify</h3><p>Confirm the affected route, API, screen, component, or mobile flow. Map the finding to CWE-89 and A03:2021 Injection. Inspect controllers/routes, middleware, template rendering, client-side sinks, and storage/download handlers. Trace every path where user input reaches an interpreter, parser, query builder, serializer, shell, or template engine.</p>
      <h3>Source/code targets</h3><p>Routes/controllers, middleware, template/view layer, frontend components, file handlers, authentication/session modules, authorization policies, export/report code, HTTP client/integration code.</p>
      <h3>Search commands</h3><pre>rg -n &quot;raw\(|whereRaw|query\(|execute\(|FromSqlRaw|\.raw\(|extra\(|\$where|find\(req\.|filter=.*req&quot; src app server</pre>
      <h3>Safe sample verification</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><b>Input:</b> Submit a harmless metacharacter such as a single quote in a search/login parameter in a test account.</li>
        <li><b>Expected vulnerable result:</b> HTTP 500, database/LDAP error, changed result count, or different authentication behavior.</li>
        <li><b>Expected fixed result:</b> HTTP 200/400 with a generic validation message; no backend error details; query logic unchanged.</li>
      </ul>
      <pre>curl -i &quot;https://app.example.test/search?q=%27&quot;</pre>
      <h3>Code-level remediation</h3><p>Use parameterized queries / ORM; least-privilege DB accounts. Replace string concatenation with structured APIs, parameterized queries, allowlists, safe parsers, and least-privilege runtime accounts.</p>
      <h3>Review flow</h3><pre>Untrusted input -&gt; schema validation -&gt; safe structured API/parser -&gt; encoded output or parameterized execution -&gt; monitored failure handling</pre>
    </div>
  </article>
<article class="finding" data-domain="Web" data-severity="Low" data-text="kb-2 missing security headers responses lack important browser security headers such as content-security-policy, strict-transport-security, x-frame-options, x-content-type-options, or referrer-policy. increases exposure to clickjacking, mime sniffing, downgrade attacks, and client-side injection impact. implement a hardened baseline of http security headers appropriate to the application and test for regressions in ci/cd. cwe-693 a05:2021 security misconfiguration">
