<article class="finding" data-domain="Web" data-severity="High" data-text="kb-3 cross-site scripting (reflected) user-controlled input is reflected in the response without sufficient output encoding or sanitization. an attacker may execute javascript in a victim browser, steal session data, perform actions as the user, or alter page content. apply context-aware output encoding, validate input, sanitize trusted html with a proven library, and deploy a restrictive content-security-policy. cwe-79 a03:2021 injection">
